abstract: Dianna Duran, New Mexico's Republican Secretary of State, faces embezzlement, fraud, money laundering and campaign finance violation charges from Democrat and Attorney General Hector Balderas, intensifying tensions between them.
lead_paragraph: The attorney general’s complaint accuses Dianna Duran of embezzlement, money laundering and campaign finance violations.

headline.main: New Mexico: Secretary of State Is Accused of Corruption
headline.print_headline: A Top New Mexico Official Is Charged With Financial Misdeeds

snippet: The attorney general’s complaint accuses Dianna Duran of embezzlement, money laundering and campaign finance violations.
